SECTION X. <attbytes>64Kb</attbytes><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>BOOK</TY><ID>Z300000204</ID><A1>Amory, Thomas, 1691?-1788?</A1><T1>John Buncle (1756)</T1><PBL>Printed for J. Noon, [etc.]</PBL><Y1>1756</Y1><T2>Literature Online</T2></comcitn></comhd3>
<front>
<lg><l>Thou attribute divine! thou ray of God!</l>
<l>Immortal reason! come, and with thee bring,</l>
<l>In thy exulting train, invincible,</l>
<l>The honest purpose, and the chearful heart;</l>
<l>The joyful fancy, fill'd with images</l>
<l>Of truth, of science, and of social love.</l>
<l>There is no ground for fear, while we are good:</l>
<l>Nature's the nurse, and providence the guide.</l></lg></front>
